            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, catalytic converter cleaners can work for minor carbon and phosphorus deposits that cause sluggish performance or borderline emissions failures. They are most effective when the converter is not physically damaged or severely clogged. Products like Cataclean and Oxicat use solvent-based formulas that burn off deposits during normal driving. However, if the ceramic substrate inside the converter is melted or broken, no chemical cleaner will fix it."
          }
